<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utramddarkluxdeorum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tramddark Luxdeorum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/01 3:28:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> Lets see...besides that you can do the ring quests...the shawl quests...the first part of the phenocryst focus quest....or hand in 4 helmets to the chamberlain for a hefty hit(must be dubious at least) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/01 4:56:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't put much faith in the phenocryst quest.<br>
<br>
I spent days collecting hundreds of velium bits to run that quest over and over.  I then spend days, in fact, running that quest over and over.  I collected enough heads and toes to run the first two coldain shawl quests three times, and did.<br>
<br>
Then, last night, my guildmates had an excessively large pull while setting up for Dain.  I was intending to ignore the guards, and either /q out or &quot;forget&quot; to turn off autoattack on enrage on Dain himself to avoid faction hits, but when there's 4 royal guards, the chamberlain, and a few icewell sentries thrown in for flavor pounding my friends into pulp, it's time to screw the faction and help out.<br>
<br>
So, I smacked around a sentry to get it to stop beating on a cleric, killed it, got a Dain hit.<br>
<br>
Then I smacked another sentry.  &quot;Your faction with DainFrostreaverIV cannot get any worse.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yep, hundreds of times through that pickaxe sharpening quest wasn't sufficient to offset ONE dwarf kill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usphirekblackstaff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sphirek Blackstaff</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://gforti.homestead.com/files/square.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 7:35:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> A good frostreaver hit is off Keldor Dek`Torek behind tormax's room, drops orb of the infinate void and is on a 1-3 day spawn timer, really easy to kill and the orb rocks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/7/01 3:54:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> I'm content to wait for plan &quot;B,&quot; and hope Tormax isn't offed the second he spawns by someone 12 timezones away from me.  I think right now he's due at like 6:15:34 am on wednesdays or something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uimmortalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Immortalis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/7/01 9:32:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> I did the first two steps of the shawl quest 6 times each.  Did the first part of the phenocrist quest with the picks 154 times.  Killed Tormax once....<br>
<br>
<br>
Still threat to dain.<br>
<br>
F DAIN! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleriche1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leriche1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/01 1:24:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> Kindly to dain<br>
<br>
Did it 2 ways.  Coldain Shawl quest...7th, Coldain ring quest 9th.  I also sit in EW, use my tailoring to MQ first ring to friends, have Done 8th ring 2 or 3 times (1 to twink rest to friends), the ring hits are big, i went from indiff to amiable by completing my 9th ring.  I don't think ring 1 and 2 are very big hits...as i have done about 400 of those and really don't see much faction change.  Ring 8 is pretty good though, i also saw a faction gain from 7th shawl, but maybe that was just timing.  Key is, don't kill dorfs, if you want the dain faction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udeelit1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deelit1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/01 2:05:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> The ninth ring hit is big, as you know the faction you get from questing with someone is the opposite of killing them, meaning questing 9th ring removes one dain kill, and if you haven't killed dain you will shoot up in faction. I am apprehensive to Dain after doing 8th ring and 7th shawl so I can't say those are the best ways.<br>
<br>
Only downside to 9th ring is that it probably wipes out all your +tormax hits from killing velk in one shot.<br>
<br>
It's technically possible to be non kos to all of velious, but since dragons drop such good loot you're much better off just being non kos to dorf/giants. Kill rif to max coldain, take a hit on tormax to set dain straight if you've bottomed it. Then kill velks a few times to refresh tormax and kill in tov for zek. Then you can buy dorf heads to quest for +rif.<br>
<br>
If you're a caster you can maintain positive faction for all really easily (dorf quests don't move faction much, suicide on dain kills, kael quests aren't for casters and the few good lewtz giants can be fixed easily with your random velk/tov killings)<br>
<br>
<br>
Deedlit Elementalcaller<br>
60 Arch Magi<br>
Bertox <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzanoan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanoan </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/01 5:57:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frostreaver faction</span><hr size=1> Anyone know minimum faction to Dain, doing 9th ring? (Handing in traitor+8th rin)<br>
